# Getting Started

This guide walks you through the complete setup process for {{ project_name }}.

## System Requirements

| Requirement | Version | Notes |
|-------------|---------|-------|
| Node.js | ≥20.0.0 | LTS recommended |
| pnpm | ≥8.0.0 | Package manager |
{%- if api_module == 'enabled' and 'python' in api_languages %}
| Python | ≥3.11 | With uv package manager |
| uv | ≥0.4.0 | Fast Python package installer |
{%- endif %}
| Git | ≥2.0 | Version control |

## Installation Methods

### Method 1: Clone from GitHub

```bash
git clone https://github.com/{{ project_slug }}/{{ project_slug }}.git
cd {{ project_slug }}
pnpm install
{%- if api_module == 'enabled' and 'python' in api_languages %}
uv sync
{%- endif %}
```

### Method 2: Create from template

If you want to create a new project based on the Riso template:

```bash
copier copy gh:riso-template/riso my-new-project
cd my-new-project
```

## Configuration

After installation, configure your project:

1. Copy the example environment file:
   ```bash
   cp .env.example .env
   ```

2. Edit `.env` with your settings

3. Verify the installation:
   ```bash
   pnpm run build
   ```

## Next Steps

Continue to the [Configuration Guide](/docs/guides/configuration) to customize your setup.
